Here's a CSS rule you can use to center the text "center me" horizontally and vertically on the page:

```css
.center-me {
   position: absolute;
   top: 50%;
   left: 50%;
   transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
   text-align: center;
}
```

Assuming the text is contained in an HTML element with the class `center-me`, this rule will position the element horizontally and vertically at the center of its containing block, and align the text within it to the center. The final result will be that the text "center me" appears perfectly centered on the page.
